23/10/2005
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Police in BiH have apprehended three men suspected of terrorist activities, the Federation of BiH (FBiH) Interior Ministry announced Friday (21 October).
According to the statement, one Bosnian, one Turkish and one Swedish citizen were detained.
Police also located arms, explosives and munitions at two locations in Sarajevo, the ministry said, without elaborating.
(Dnevni avaz - 22/10/05;
PBS BiH - 21/10/05)
